WEBVTT

00:02.002 --> 00:03.252
Here's what you
missed last week.

00:03.337 --> 00:06.422
Quinn's pregnant and Puck's
the father, but everybody
thinks it's Finn.

00:06.507 --> 00:09.008
You're a punk
who doesn't deserve Quinn
as his girlfriend!

00:09.093 --> 00:12.053
Except for Quinn's parents
who don't know anything at all.

00:12.137 --> 00:13.805
They just know she's in
the Celibacy Club.

00:13.889 --> 00:16.849
Well, call the Vatican.
We got ourselves
another immaculate conception.

00:16.934 --> 00:19.310
- And that's what
you missed on—
- ♪ Glee ♪

00:20.729 --> 00:24.399
[School Bell Rings]

00:24.483 --> 00:28.069
Ballad.
From Middle English "balade."

00:30.155 --> 00:32.699
- Who knows what this word means?
- It's a male duck.

00:32.783 --> 00:36.494
- Kurt.
- A ballad is a love song.

00:36.578 --> 00:39.372
Sometimes, but they don't
always express love.

00:39.456 --> 00:41.374
Ballads are stories set
to music...

00:41.458 --> 00:44.419
which is why they're
the perfect storm
of self-expression.

00:44.503 --> 00:48.881
Stories and music are the way
we express feelings that we
can't get out any other way.

00:48.966 --> 00:51.592
Okay, now sectionals
are in a few weeks.

00:51.677 --> 00:55.263
And there's a new rule
this year. We have
to perform... a ballad.

00:55.347 --> 00:59.976
Looks like my weekly letter
to the Ohio Show Choir
Committee finally paid off.

01:00.060 --> 01:02.103
Okay, so here's our assignment
for the week.

01:02.187 --> 01:05.982
I'm gonna pair you off,
and I want you to pick a ballad
to sing to your partner.

01:06.066 --> 01:08.234
Look them right in the eye,

01:08.318 --> 01:11.571
find the emotion
you want to express,
and make them feel it.

01:11.655 --> 01:15.241
- I pick Quinn.
- No, no, no, no, no. Too easy.

01:15.325 --> 01:17.577
Your partners
will be chosen by fate.

01:17.703 --> 01:20.913
Oooh.
"Oooh," yeah. I put
all your names in this hat.

01:20.998 --> 01:23.040
Whoever you choose
is your partner.

01:23.125 --> 01:26.377
- I bet that duck's in the hat.
- But Matt's out sick today.

01:26.462 --> 01:29.756
He had to go to the hospital
'cause they found a spider
in his ear.

01:29.840 --> 01:33.301
- [Students Groan]
- I guess I'll just have to put
my name in the hat for now.

01:33.385 --> 01:35.970
Who's up first?

01:38.891 --> 01:41.017
- Mercedes.
- [Will] All right.

01:42.394 --> 01:44.687
Quinn.

01:47.149 --> 01:50.860
- Kurt.
- [Students Laugh]

01:50.944 --> 01:52.987
Mr. Schue, I don't know
if I can do this
with another guy.

01:53.071 --> 01:55.239
The Fates have spoken, Finn.

01:56.366 --> 01:58.993
Other Asian.

01:59.077 --> 02:00.828
[Chuckles]
Brittany.

02:00.913 --> 02:02.413
[Gasps]

02:02.498 --> 02:05.666
- [Will] How fitting.
- [Brittany] Yea!

02:05.751 --> 02:07.710
Looks like I get you,
Mr. Schue.

02:09.213 --> 02:12.715
Uh, you know what?
Maybe we should just wait
until Matt gets back.

02:12.800 --> 02:16.177
- The Fates talked, Mr. Schue.
- [Students Laugh]

02:16.261 --> 02:18.930
Would you mind clarifying
what kinds of songs
you want us to sing?

02:19.014 --> 02:22.391
Why don't you let
Mr. Schuester and I demonstrate?

02:22.476 --> 02:25.394
Brad, "Endless Love"
in B-flat, please.
It's my favorite duet.

02:25.479 --> 02:28.481
I really don't think
that's an appropriate
song, Rachel.

02:28.565 --> 02:31.400
Why? It's a great song
and it's a perfect ballad.

02:31.485 --> 02:35.363
Yeah, I really like
that song, Mr. Schue.

02:35.447 --> 02:37.782
[Students Laugh]

02:37.866 --> 02:40.493
♪♪ [Slow Tempo]

02:42.412 --> 02:45.373
♪ My love ♪

02:45.457 --> 02:48.000
[Thinking]
I could totally sing
this song with Finn.

02:48.085 --> 02:50.795
But screw him
if he thinks he's taking
the Diana Ross part from me.

02:50.879 --> 02:54.841
♪ The only thing
that's right ♪

02:54.925 --> 02:57.093
[Thinking]
I love the days
when I don't wear underwear.

02:57.177 --> 02:59.220
Full commando.
♪ My first love ♪

02:59.304 --> 03:01.597
[Thinking]
I never noticed how nice
Rachel's butt is.

03:01.682 --> 03:03.933
Oh, crap. I think Quinn
knows I'm staring at it.

03:04.017 --> 03:06.435
♪ You're every breath
that I take ♪

03:06.520 --> 03:12.483
♪ You're every step I make ♪

03:12.568 --> 03:14.569
♪ And I ♪

03:14.653 --> 03:16.571
♪ I-I-I ♪

03:16.655 --> 03:19.782
♪ I want to share ♪

03:19.867 --> 03:23.327
[Both]
♪ All my love ♪

03:23.412 --> 03:26.372
♪ With you ♪

03:26.456 --> 03:32.211
[Solo]
♪ No one else will do ♪

03:32.296 --> 03:36.632
- ♪ And your eyes ♪
- ♪ Your eyes, your eyes ♪

03:36.717 --> 03:42.930
[Both]
♪ They tell me how much
you care ♪

03:43.015 --> 03:45.266
♪ Oh, yeah ♪

03:45.350 --> 03:48.311
[Thinking]
Wow. I've never noticed
this before...

03:48.395 --> 03:50.396
because he's always trying
to destroy my career,

03:50.480 --> 03:52.398
but Mr. Schue has
really pretty eyes.

03:52.482 --> 03:55.735
♪ My endless love ♪

03:55.819 --> 03:59.030
And really nice teeth.
He's obviously invested
in good oral hygiene.

03:59.114 --> 04:02.158
And that's important to me.
It shows wonderful
self-esteem.

04:02.242 --> 04:05.077
[Both]
♪ I'll be that fool ♪

04:05.162 --> 04:08.247
♪ For you ♪

04:08.332 --> 04:11.375
♪ I'm sure ♪

04:11.460 --> 04:14.045
[Thinking]
I don't like the way
she's looking at me.

04:14.129 --> 04:18.925
Oh, I shouldn't have sung
this song to her. Crap!
She looks crazy right now.

04:19.009 --> 04:20.551
I know this look.

04:20.636 --> 04:23.262
♪ And yes ♪

04:23.347 --> 04:28.434
♪ You'll be the only one ♪

04:28.518 --> 04:30.603
- ♪ Oh ♪
- ♪ 'Cause no ♪

04:30.687 --> 04:33.731
[Both]
♪ No one can deny ♪

04:33.815 --> 04:36.108
♪ This love ♪

04:36.193 --> 04:39.153
♪ I have inside ♪

04:39.237 --> 04:41.238
♪ And I'll give ♪

04:41.323 --> 04:44.367
♪ It all to you ♪

04:44.451 --> 04:48.120
- ♪ My love ♪
- ♪ My love, my love ♪

04:48.205 --> 04:53.793
[Both]
♪ My endless love ♪♪

04:53.877 --> 04:55.586
[Thinking]
Okay, this is amazing.

04:55.671 --> 05:00.091
When I'm singing with him,
it's like I'm seeing him
for the first time.

05:00.175 --> 05:04.679
And what I'm seeing
is super, super cute.

05:05.764 --> 05:07.473
♪♪ [Ends]

05:07.599 --> 05:09.558
Okay. Something like that.
[Applause]

05:09.643 --> 05:13.020
[Nervous Laugh,
Clears Throat]

05:19.027 --> 05:23.114
Sweetie, I am so proud of you.

05:24.658 --> 05:28.536
The Chastity Ball is
so important to your father.

05:28.620 --> 05:32.123
[Thinking] God, I miss
the firm support of my
polyester Cheerios uniform.

05:32.207 --> 05:34.709
The control panel hid
my baby bump perfectly.

05:34.793 --> 05:39.130
Hmm. That's odd. We had this
custom-made a month ago.

05:39.214 --> 05:41.549
I had a really big lunch
today at school.

05:41.633 --> 05:43.634
Really big tacos.

05:47.514 --> 05:51.100
No worries, sweetie.
I'll just take it down
to the tailor tomorrow.

05:51.184 --> 05:54.854
We'll let it out a little bit.
The problem here, honey,
is, you know,

05:54.938 --> 05:57.982
I just don't think you've been
getting enough exercise ever
since you quit the Cheerios.

05:58.108 --> 06:00.234
Am I right?
Yeah, yeah. That's right.

06:00.318 --> 06:04.030
You used to spend hours
every day doing backflips
and high kicks.

06:04.114 --> 06:06.991
And now- I mean, now you spend
all your free time...

06:07.075 --> 06:09.952
sitting on a stool in the dark
singing show tunes.

06:10.037 --> 06:13.122
Do you know how many calories
you burn singing? Hmm?

06:13.248 --> 06:16.542
Not very many.
Judy! Glenn Beck is on.

06:16.626 --> 06:19.670
- [Gasps]
- Oh, wait. Hold on.

06:19.796 --> 06:22.715
[Laughs] He's so-
Hold on.
No, I don't want to see.

06:22.799 --> 06:24.717
Daddy, it's not like
we're getting married.

06:24.801 --> 06:28.220
I don't want— Oh.
[Laughs]

06:28.305 --> 06:31.223
Oh! Look at you.

06:31.308 --> 06:33.392
Speaking of getting married,

06:33.477 --> 06:36.896
how's that boy
you've been dating?

06:36.980 --> 06:39.356
Yeah, yeah. He's not pressuring
you at all, is he?

06:39.441 --> 06:42.359
No. No, he's
a gentleman.

06:42.444 --> 06:46.322
I'm glad to hear that.
That's why I'm inviting him
over for dinner on Sunday.

06:46.448 --> 06:48.783
Oh, wonderful!
Refresher?

06:48.867 --> 06:51.744
Honey, I don't want you
to lift a finger for me.

06:51.828 --> 06:54.747
I'm your wife.
[Chuckles]

06:54.873 --> 06:57.875
My little lemon drop.
I gotta go catch Glenn.
[Gasps]

06:57.959 --> 06:59.960
[Clears Throat]

07:01.630 --> 07:03.255
[Sighs]

07:03.340 --> 07:05.758
[School Bell Rings]

07:05.842 --> 07:07.593
Mr. Schuester?
Yeah?

07:07.677 --> 07:11.055
I just wanted to confirm
we're set to rehearse our ballad
at 4:00 sharp this afternoon.

07:11.139 --> 07:14.016
Oh. Isn't Matt back yet?

07:14.101 --> 07:17.978
No, it's just...
you and me all week long.

07:20.398 --> 07:23.109
Great. I'll see you at 4:00.

07:26.696 --> 07:28.614
Is there something else?

07:28.698 --> 07:30.825
I just wanted
to give you this.

07:34.746 --> 07:36.247
Open it.

07:38.083 --> 07:41.252
Gold stars are kind of
my signature thing.

07:41.336 --> 07:45.965
I figure every time you wear it
you can think of me and the star
you're helping me become.

07:47.634 --> 07:50.511
- [Will]
It's happening... again.
- [School Bell Rings]

07:50.595 --> 07:53.931
It always starts
with a novelty gift.

07:54.015 --> 07:56.100
Well, you can't
blame her, Will.

07:56.184 --> 07:58.310
If we were gonna rank
crush-worthy teachers
at this school,

07:58.395 --> 08:01.063
you'd be number one
with a bullet.

08:03.275 --> 08:07.236
Uh, well, I-I- When did-
When did this start
with Rachel?

08:07.320 --> 08:10.489
We sang a duet in Glee Club.
"Endless Love."

08:10.615 --> 08:15.411
Okay. In hindsight,
that was probably a mistake.
Yeah.

08:15.495 --> 08:17.621
I can't handle
going through this again.

08:17.706 --> 08:20.249
Sorry. Going through, um-
Going through what again?

08:20.333 --> 08:25.045
Have I ever told you about...
Suzy Pepper?

08:26.965 --> 08:30.384
The alpacas start there
and travel down towards
Guadalajara.

08:30.468 --> 08:35.222
Suzy Pepper wasn't
the first schoolgirl crush,
but she was the hardest.

08:35.307 --> 08:38.225
It happened about two years ago
before you were a teacher here.

08:38.310 --> 08:41.520
Suzy was unique.
Mr. Schue?

08:41.605 --> 08:45.441
How do you conjugate
the verb "to love"?

08:49.112 --> 08:51.155
[School Bell Rings]

08:56.953 --> 08:58.537
Peppers.

08:58.622 --> 09:02.333
So you can wear them
and think of me—
Suzy Pepper.

09:02.417 --> 09:06.003
[Will] I thought it would
burn out like the others.
But it only got worse.

09:06.087 --> 09:08.589
[Phone Rings]

09:08.673 --> 09:11.175
Hello?
[Exhaling]

09:11.301 --> 09:14.553
Who is it? Who died?
[Exhaling]

09:14.638 --> 09:16.555
Suzy Pepper?

09:16.640 --> 09:19.600
You knew it was me
just by the sound
of my breath.

09:19.684 --> 09:22.311
That's so romantic.

09:22.395 --> 09:24.563
Listen, you little psycho.
This is Will's wife.

09:24.648 --> 09:26.857
And if I don't get enough sleep,
my antidepressants won't work.

09:26.983 --> 09:29.318
And then I'll go crazy,
and I'll kill you.
Terri.

09:29.402 --> 09:31.320
Stop calling!

09:31.446 --> 09:35.407
[Phone Beeps Off]
[Sighs]
Can't you handle anything, Will?

09:35.492 --> 09:37.409
[Will]
Terri was right.
[School Bell Rings]

09:37.494 --> 09:39.912
Or so I thought.

09:39.996 --> 09:43.666
I decided
to be honest with Suzy.
Face this head-on.

09:43.792 --> 09:46.335
Okay, how'd that go?
[Sighs]

09:46.419 --> 09:49.588
[Sobbing]
♪♪ [Slow]

09:49.673 --> 09:51.590
[Gasps]

09:51.675 --> 09:54.677
[Sobbing Continues]

09:57.013 --> 10:00.766
♪ More than words ♪

10:00.850 --> 10:03.852
♪ Is all you have to do ♪

10:03.937 --> 10:06.855
♪ To make it real ♪
[Alarm Wailing]

10:11.653 --> 10:13.862
♪ That you love ♪♪

10:16.408 --> 10:18.325
[Gags]

10:18.410 --> 10:20.369
It was the world's
hottest pepper.

10:20.495 --> 10:23.539
She had it shipped
from Sinaloa, Mexico.
Oh, gosh. What happened?

10:23.623 --> 10:27.126
The ambulance arrived
just in time. The pepper
burned holes in her esophagus,

10:27.210 --> 10:30.045
and she was in a medically
induced coma for three days.

10:30.130 --> 10:32.798
That's why I can't
just tell Rachel to back off.

10:32.882 --> 10:34.800
These girls are too fragile.

10:34.884 --> 10:36.844
Wow. Okay.

10:36.928 --> 10:39.555
How 'bout this?
Why don't you take
your own advice?

10:39.639 --> 10:41.557
Right? Do what you told
the kids to do.

10:41.641 --> 10:44.351
If you’re feeling awkward
telling Rachel how you feel,

10:44.436 --> 10:47.396
then why don't you, um,
you know, sing it to her.

10:47.480 --> 10:50.024
Let her down gently.

10:50.108 --> 10:52.651
And don't wear that tie.

10:52.736 --> 10:54.320
Yeah.

10:54.404 --> 10:58.240
Sing to me
everything you feel.

10:59.492 --> 11:03.871
Okay. Uh-

11:07.500 --> 11:09.460
I can't. I can't—
I can't sing to a dude.

11:09.586 --> 11:11.754
You have to try.
I can't! Okay?

11:11.838 --> 11:16.342
I can't! I'm sick
and tired of people pushing
me to be somebody I'm not.

11:19.137 --> 11:23.474
Your lashing out at me
is fantastically compelling
and inappropriate.

11:23.558 --> 11:26.518
Dude, I'm sorry.

11:26.603 --> 11:29.271
You're really awesome,
Kurt. I-

11:29.356 --> 11:31.398
I'm just under
a load of crap right now.

11:31.483 --> 11:33.567
Girls.

11:33.651 --> 11:36.278
They're your problem.

11:36.363 --> 11:39.782
They're up.
They're down. Girls.

11:48.416 --> 11:50.626
It's the baby.
[Exhales]

11:51.878 --> 11:53.629
She's my daughter and-

11:55.465 --> 11:59.009
There are so many things
I want to say to her,
and I'm never gonna be able to.

12:00.762 --> 12:02.513
Like what?

12:02.597 --> 12:05.224
Well,

12:05.308 --> 12:09.645
like how I don't want her
to think that her father
just abandoned her.

12:09.729 --> 12:11.647
How I would do anything
for her.

12:11.731 --> 12:16.360
How no matter what I do
I'm always thinking about her.

12:16.444 --> 12:20.697
How I'm gonna spend
my whole life loving her
and she's never even gonna know.

12:22.700 --> 12:24.660
You gotta let it out.

12:29.124 --> 12:31.417
How?

12:31.501 --> 12:34.378
By singing.

12:34.462 --> 12:37.172
"I'll Stand By You,"
by the Pretenders.

12:37.257 --> 12:41.135
It's in your wheelhouse.
And I know you know it from
the radio because it's a classic.

12:41.219 --> 12:44.972
And you do well
with classics, especially
in the soft rock mode.

12:45.056 --> 12:48.600
Yeah, I do like
that song, but...

12:48.685 --> 12:51.270
how's it gonna make me
feel better again?

12:51.354 --> 12:54.523
By singing it out
to the audience.

12:55.775 --> 12:59.027
Imagine your little girl
sitting there.

13:00.321 --> 13:03.240
Thank God I never missed
a piano lesson.

13:07.036 --> 13:11.206
♪♪ [Piano]

13:15.545 --> 13:18.088
♪ Oh ♪

13:18.173 --> 13:21.592
♪ Why you look so sad ♪

13:21.676 --> 13:25.137
♪ Tears are in your eyes ♪

13:25.221 --> 13:29.475
♪ Come on and come to me now ♪

13:29.559 --> 13:33.020
♪ When the night falls on you ♪

13:33.104 --> 13:35.939
♪ You don't know
what to do ♪

13:36.024 --> 13:39.151
♪ Nothing you confess ♪

13:39.235 --> 13:42.279
♪ Could make me
love you less ♪

13:42.363 --> 13:45.824
♪ I'll stand by you ♪

13:45.909 --> 13:49.411
♪ I'll stand by you ♪

13:49.496 --> 13:53.248
♪ Won't let nobody hurt you ♪

13:53.333 --> 13:56.835
♪ I'll stand by you ♪

13:56.920 --> 14:00.464
♪ Take me in into
your darkest hour ♪

14:00.548 --> 14:03.550
♪ And I'll never desert you ♪

14:03.635 --> 14:07.471
♪ I'll stand by you ♪

14:07.555 --> 14:11.099
♪ I'll stand by you ♪

14:11.184 --> 14:14.686
♪ Won't let nobody hurt you ♪

14:14.771 --> 14:19.900
♪ I'll stand by you ♪♪

14:19.901 --> 14:20.025
♪ I'll stand by you ♪♪

14:20.109 --> 14:22.110
Finn, what's going on?

14:28.910 --> 14:31.119
What are you doing?
Uh, nothing.

14:36.042 --> 14:38.168
Were you just singing
to a sonogram?

14:39.254 --> 14:40.671
Uh-huh.

14:57.438 --> 14:59.439
Is Quinn pregnant?

15:00.441 --> 15:02.985
[Sobbing]
Mom. I'm sorry.

15:03.111 --> 15:05.821
I'm so sorry!
[Sobbing Continues]
Shh, shh.

15:05.947 --> 15:09.032
I screwed up, Mom.
It's gonna be okay.

15:10.451 --> 15:12.995
[Sobbing Continues]
I'm so sorry.
Shh, shh. Shh.

15:16.958 --> 15:19.376
[School Bell Rings]
I can't believe you told your mom.
What if she tells my mom?

15:19.502 --> 15:22.879
She's not.
Half the school knows. Your mom
knows. Who else you wanna tell?

15:23.006 --> 15:26.091
She's not gonna tell anybody.
You're wrong. I'm right.
I'm smart. You're dumb.

15:26.175 --> 15:29.428
All this baby drama is making
my rosacea act up.

15:29.512 --> 15:33.056
I know. I just feel bad
for them, having to
go through this on their own.

15:33.141 --> 15:35.475
Let me see what I can do.
I'll report back later.

15:35.560 --> 15:37.644
[Quinn]
No, no, no. You're wrong.
I'm right. I'm right.

15:37.770 --> 15:39.771
She doesn't talk
to other moms.
Okay?

15:41.733 --> 15:46.028
[Exhales]
How do you explain her
constant irritation with you?

15:46.112 --> 15:48.405
It's because she's a girl.

15:48.489 --> 15:52.451
No, I think it's the pregnancy
hormones or something.
They make her kinda nuts.

15:52.535 --> 15:55.495
It's enough to wanna
give up women altogether.
[Laughs]

15:55.580 --> 16:00.083
Yeah. Anyway, thanks for
the advice about singing
to the baby like that.

16:00.168 --> 16:03.837
It worked like a charm.
I owe you one, dude.

16:06.215 --> 16:10.093
[Thinking]
Okay, I'll admit it.
I'm madly in love with Finn.

16:10.178 --> 16:12.220
I have been since
the first time we met.

16:16.059 --> 16:19.269
Dude, impulse control.

16:19.354 --> 16:21.313
He was my knight
in shining armor.

16:21.397 --> 16:24.483
My feelings only grew stronger
as we bonded over Glee,

16:24.567 --> 16:26.485
then football,
then skin care.

16:26.569 --> 16:29.988
Your "T" zone is
dangerously dry.

16:30.073 --> 16:32.240
Your "T" zone.

16:32.325 --> 16:34.660
Oh.
[Chuckles]

16:34.744 --> 16:38.747
Twice a day. It's very mild
and has a built-in
sunblock.

16:38.831 --> 16:41.875
Cool. Thanks, man.

16:41.959 --> 16:44.836
[Thinking]
I don't know why I find
his stupidity charming.

16:44.921 --> 16:48.256
I mean, he's cheating off
a girl who thinks the square
root of four is rainbows.

16:48.341 --> 16:50.967
I guess that's love for you.

16:51.052 --> 16:53.303
Hey, eyes on
your own paper.

16:53.388 --> 16:56.890
I know it seems weird
that I'm helping Finn
with Quinn.

16:56.974 --> 16:59.851
But rest assured,
it's all part of a master plan.

16:59.936 --> 17:02.479
No matter what I do or how much
I assist him with his ballad,

17:02.563 --> 17:04.564
she's going to end up
disappointing him
and breaking his heart.

17:04.649 --> 17:07.526
And then he'll be crying
into my shoulder pads.

17:08.611 --> 17:09.611
[School Bell Rings]

17:09.612 --> 17:10.529
[School Bell Rings]

17:10.613 --> 17:12.239
[Sniffs]

17:12.365 --> 17:15.409
[Soft Gasp]
Okay, so,
I'm really excited.

17:15.493 --> 17:18.578
I picked a medley of songs
that's gonna be
a fantastic teaching tool...

17:18.663 --> 17:20.163
about how to sing
a great ballad.

17:20.289 --> 17:23.125
Why is Miss Pillsbury here?
Uh-

17:23.209 --> 17:27.087
Well, I- I, too,
am very curious
about the power of the ballad.

17:27.171 --> 17:30.132
You know, I'm thinking
of doing some career
counseling in song.

17:30.258 --> 17:31.550
Emma.
S.A.T. prep-

17:31.676 --> 17:34.177
Just— Yeah.
Sitting. Yeah.

17:34.262 --> 17:38.849
Okay, Rachel. This is a mash-up
of "Young Girl" by
Gary Puckett & the Union Gap...

17:38.933 --> 17:41.518
and the 1980 Police classic,
"Don't Stand So Close To Me."

17:41.602 --> 17:43.729
And I want you to listen
very closely to the lyrics...

17:43.813 --> 17:45.856
because I really mean
what I'm singing.

17:47.775 --> 17:49.818
Really... listen.

17:51.279 --> 17:53.238
Okay.

17:53.239 --> 17:53.447
Okay.

17:53.531 --> 17:56.992
♪♪ ["Don't Stand
So Close To Me"]

18:00.663 --> 18:03.790
♪ Young teacher
The subject ♪

18:03.875 --> 18:07.335
♪ Of schoolgirl fantasy ♪

18:07.420 --> 18:10.630
♪ She wants him so badly ♪

18:10.715 --> 18:14.301
♪ Knows what she wants to be ♪

18:14.427 --> 18:18.889
♪♪ ["Young Girl"]
♪ With all the charms
of a woman ♪

18:21.476 --> 18:26.480
♪ You've kept the secret
of your youth ♪

18:28.232 --> 18:31.109
♪♪ [Song Switches Back]
♪ Bookmark it
She's so close now ♪

18:31.194 --> 18:34.029
♪ This girl is half his age ♪

18:34.113 --> 18:38.074
♪ Don't stand
Don't stand so ♪

18:38.159 --> 18:41.453
♪ Don't stand
so close to me ♪

18:41.579 --> 18:45.081
♪♪ [Song Switches Back]
♪ Young girl
you're outta your mind ♪

18:45.166 --> 18:48.335
♪ Your love for me
is way out of line ♪

18:48.419 --> 18:50.253
♪ Better run, girl ♪

18:50.338 --> 18:54.674
♪ You're much too young, girl ♪

18:54.801 --> 18:59.262
♪♪ [Song Switches Back]
♪ Temptation, frustration ♪

18:59.388 --> 19:02.474
♪ So bad it makes him cry ♪
♪♪ [Song Switches Back]

19:02.558 --> 19:07.062
♪ Beneath your perfume
and makeup ♪

19:09.106 --> 19:16.112
♪ You're just a baby
in disguise ♪

19:16.197 --> 19:18.615
♪ Get out of here ♪

19:18.699 --> 19:23.078
♪ Before you have the time
to change your mind ♪

19:23.162 --> 19:29.334
♪ 'Cause I'm afraid
you'll go too far ♪

19:29.460 --> 19:32.838
♪♪ [Song Switches Back]
♪ Don't stand
Don't stand so ♪

19:32.922 --> 19:36.174
♪ Don't stand
so close to me ♪

19:36.300 --> 19:39.845
♪♪ [Song Switches Back]
♪ Young girl
you're outta your mind ♪

19:39.929 --> 19:42.430
♪ Your love for me
is way out of line ♪

19:42.557 --> 19:47.602
♪ Better run, girl ♪
[Chorus]
♪ Don't stand so ♪

19:49.146 --> 19:54.776
♪ You're much
too young, girl ♪♪

20:01.117 --> 20:03.493
So, Rachel,

20:03.578 --> 20:06.663
do you think you understood
the message I was trying
to get across with that ballad?

20:06.747 --> 20:10.917
Yes. It means I'm very young
and it's hard for you
to stand close to me.

20:11.002 --> 20:13.420
[Sighs]
Oh, no. Um-

20:13.504 --> 20:17.340
Emma, would you mind
helping me out here? Was that
the message that you got?

20:17.425 --> 20:20.677
- You're a very good performer.
- [Groans]

20:20.761 --> 20:24.055
- He's very good.
- Well, I, for one,
can't wait to go home...

20:24.140 --> 20:26.057
and work on a medley
of my own for tomorrow.

20:26.142 --> 20:29.728
Because this lesson
has given me...
a lot to think about.

20:29.812 --> 20:33.023
No, Rachel, that really
wasn't the— You—

20:34.483 --> 20:36.026
[Sighs]

20:36.152 --> 20:37.986
[School Bell Rings]
Bravo.

20:46.287 --> 20:48.872
Thanks for coming over,
Kurt.

20:48.956 --> 20:51.416
I know you're into fashion
and that kind of stuff.

20:51.500 --> 20:54.961
And I need to find
something nice to wear
to the Fabrays for dinner. So-

20:55.046 --> 20:58.131
I couldn't be more pleased
and honored to help you find
something vintage...

20:58.215 --> 21:01.217
and appropriate to wear.

21:01.302 --> 21:06.806
Here it is.
My mom never had the heart
to throw this stuff out.

21:08.559 --> 21:10.602
[Chuckles]

21:10.686 --> 21:14.356
Here, hang on to that
for the next time Puck
throws you in the Dumpster.

21:15.524 --> 21:17.442
My dad's the same way.

21:17.526 --> 21:21.863
My mom died 10 years ago and
he still keeps her toothbrush
on the holder by their sink.

21:23.866 --> 21:27.744
The broken dresser in their room
still smells like her perfume.

21:27.828 --> 21:30.956
I know it's stupid,
but sometimes
I'll sneak in there...

21:31.040 --> 21:33.124
and open all the drawers...

21:33.209 --> 21:37.837
and lie on the floor
and close my eyes
and just smell her.

21:37.922 --> 21:39.923
That's not stupid.

21:43.803 --> 21:47.764
I guess in a way
I'm lucky I never knew him.
You know?

21:52.728 --> 21:54.854
[Chuckles]

21:54.981 --> 21:57.565
Check this out.
[Laughs]

22:00.486 --> 22:02.028
Not half bad.

22:03.739 --> 22:05.949
Your father had good taste.

22:06.033 --> 22:08.034
I can't believe it fits.

22:14.417 --> 22:17.127
Um, thanks.

22:25.177 --> 22:28.763
My father was brave enough
to fight in some desert
thousands of miles away,

22:28.848 --> 22:33.184
and I can't even go over
to Dudley Road and tell
the Fabrays the truth.

22:35.104 --> 22:38.189
Your father didn't charge
into the breach
empty-handed.

22:38.274 --> 22:40.525
He had a weapon.

22:40.609 --> 22:43.069
You think I should
bring a gun?

22:44.405 --> 22:47.532
No. I think you should
use your greatest weapon.

22:47.616 --> 22:50.118
Your voice.

22:57.126 --> 22:59.127
Hey, sweetie, I'm home.

23:04.467 --> 23:06.468
Something smells good.

23:13.476 --> 23:15.477
[Sighs]

23:18.272 --> 23:21.191
Oh, thanks.
You're welcome.

23:21.275 --> 23:24.486
Casserole's almost ready.
Hope you like venison.

23:29.825 --> 23:31.743
Why did you even
let her in the house?

23:31.827 --> 23:33.912
'Cause she said she was
one of your Glee kids.

23:33.996 --> 23:37.123
It didn't take me five minutes
to realize she's in love
with you.

23:37.208 --> 23:40.043
She asked if she could see
your baby pictures.

23:40.127 --> 23:42.462
What? So, now you're making her
clean our bathroom?

23:42.546 --> 23:45.423
Look, Will, I've been dealing
with these schoolgirl
crushes for years.

23:45.508 --> 23:47.801
So why shouldn't I get
a little something out of it?

23:47.885 --> 23:52.263
- Do you have any more Ajax?
- In the linen closet, sweetie.

23:52.348 --> 23:53.973
[Mouths Word]

23:55.518 --> 23:58.394
This is immoral, Terri.
No, honey.
You know what's immoral?

23:58.479 --> 24:00.396
Is me having to deal
with the fact...

24:00.481 --> 24:03.149
that my husband spends
all day with young girls
who are perkier...

24:03.234 --> 24:05.693
and younger than I am.

24:05.778 --> 24:10.323
I have a rash on my belly
from that cocoa butter
that your mother sent me.

24:10.407 --> 24:12.575
Do you have any idea
how much it burns
when I sweat?

24:12.660 --> 24:15.245
I can't scrub the floors
as hard as she can.

24:15.329 --> 24:18.289
Baby, if it's that bad,
you have to let me see it.
It might be infected.

24:18.374 --> 24:21.793
What? So, now I'm gonna
show you the bleeding pustules
on my skin?

24:21.877 --> 24:25.421
Wow. Yeah. No, that's not
gonna send you into the loving
arms of some teenage slut.

24:25.506 --> 24:27.966
For the last time,
I am not having an affair
with any of my students.

24:28.050 --> 24:30.468
And you are not allowed
to turn one of them
into your slave...

24:30.553 --> 24:32.762
because you have this
irrational fear of me
leaving you.

24:32.847 --> 24:35.765
Well, why not, huh,
if it's win-win for everyone?

24:35.891 --> 24:39.018
Look, she's a really
good cook. Try it.
[Groans]

24:39.103 --> 24:41.563
- Where you going?
- I'm taking Rachel home.

24:41.647 --> 24:44.315
Can you ask her
to dust the blinds
in the craft room first?

24:44.441 --> 24:48.611
Mr. Schuester?
Yes, Rachel.

24:48.696 --> 24:50.780
Why do I have to sit
in the backseat?

24:50.865 --> 24:54.868
Um, it's the law.
Children have to ride
in the back.

24:54.952 --> 24:56.870
Children under seven.

24:56.954 --> 24:59.372
Well, I'm just concerned
for your safety.

25:00.708 --> 25:02.417
Really?

25:02.501 --> 25:06.880
Um, no. Not really.

25:09.842 --> 25:13.011
I think we should take
advantage of this golden alone
time and practice our ballad.

25:13.095 --> 25:16.347
That would be great,
but I don't have any music
in the car.

25:16.432 --> 25:18.600
It's okay. I made us a CD.

25:19.810 --> 25:21.811
Oh.

25:23.272 --> 25:26.566
♪♪ [Dance Pop]
♪ Ah, crush ♪

25:27.860 --> 25:30.028
♪ Ah ♪

25:30.112 --> 25:32.947
♪ I see ya blowin' me a kiss ♪

25:33.032 --> 25:35.450
♪ It doesn't take a scientist ♪

25:35.534 --> 25:38.411
♪ To understand
what's going on, baby ♪♪

25:38.537 --> 25:40.538
[Ejects CD]
[Sighs]

25:40.623 --> 25:43.208
I wasn't finished.

25:43.292 --> 25:47.587
Yeah, well, the acoustics
are horrible in the car.
Put your seat belt back on.

25:47.671 --> 25:50.715
[Sighs]
So, how's it going
with Puck?

25:50.841 --> 25:52.967
Are you guys
still seeing each other?
I broke things off.

25:53.052 --> 25:57.597
He was too immature. As are
all the boys in high school.

25:57.681 --> 26:00.600
I need a man who can keep
up with me intellectually
and creatively.

26:00.684 --> 26:04.229
Well, that's a tough road
for most high-school boys.

26:06.523 --> 26:08.816
That's why I have my sights
set much higher.

26:15.908 --> 26:18.117
[School Bell Rings]

26:18.202 --> 26:22.580
Stay away from him.
You're gonna get hurt... bad.

26:22.706 --> 26:26.501
You can't threaten me, Pepper.
I'm not afraid of you.
You should be.

26:30.005 --> 26:34.008
Oh, you're on the second floor?
Oh, you're right above me.

26:34.093 --> 26:37.553
Girl, you?
I'm a hot, damn mess.

26:37.638 --> 26:41.641
I found out today my hamster
is pregnant in biology class
and I just started weeping.

26:43.018 --> 26:44.936
No, no, I think
that's a great idea.

26:45.062 --> 26:48.856
We're supposed to be
rehearsing.
I'm talking to Tina.

26:48.941 --> 26:52.235
I'll hit you back.
This is bad, dude.

26:52.319 --> 26:54.654
All our ballads are terrible
'cause we're all so distracted.

26:54.738 --> 26:57.198
We're all worried about Finn
and Quinn and "babygate."

26:57.283 --> 26:59.909
We can't even sing
about our emotions 'cause
we're so worried about theirs.

27:00.035 --> 27:03.454
Who cares?
Um, we all do.

27:03.539 --> 27:07.458
So we decided we're all
gonna sing them a ballad
to show that we got their backs.

27:07.543 --> 27:10.545
Are you kidding me?
There's no way
I'm singing to them.

27:10.629 --> 27:13.172
[Groans]
It's not fair!
Finn gets everything.

27:13.257 --> 27:16.801
- He gets the sympathy.
He gets the girl.
- What is your problem?

27:16.885 --> 27:18.970
Finn's not the father!

27:19.054 --> 27:21.180
I am.

27:22.683 --> 27:25.393
What?

27:28.605 --> 27:30.523
All right, look.

27:30.607 --> 27:33.359
You need to get something
through your Mohawk
real quick.

27:33.444 --> 27:36.821
You're the baby's daddy.
It takes a hell of a lot more
to be a father.

27:36.905 --> 27:40.700
And that role's
already been cast
because Quinn chose Finn.

27:40.784 --> 27:42.702
And you need to accept that
and move on.

27:42.786 --> 27:47.582
'Cause you have no business
messing up that girl's life
any more than you already have.

27:47.666 --> 27:52.086
You need to back off.
You owe her at least that much.

28:00.929 --> 28:04.474
Mmm. A lovely ham.

28:04.600 --> 28:06.893
Thank you.
There is no beating
Judy's ham.

28:06.977 --> 28:09.270
[Laughs]
I cure all my own meats.

28:15.694 --> 28:18.988
- I'd like to propose a toast.
- Daddy, no.

28:19.114 --> 28:22.992
Russell and
his famous toasts.
[Russell Laughs]

28:23.077 --> 28:26.579
The Fabrays
are a tight-knit family.

28:26.663 --> 28:29.540
I have been blessed
with a loving wife,

28:29.625 --> 28:32.418
two remarkable daughters.

28:32.503 --> 28:35.713
My first married
a wonderful Christian man.

28:35.798 --> 28:38.007
Owns his own chain
of U.P.S. stores.

28:38.092 --> 28:40.760
My second daughter,
little Quinny,

28:40.844 --> 28:43.805
we're just so proud of her.

28:43.889 --> 28:48.684
Captain of the Cheerios,
president of
the Celibacy Club.

28:48.769 --> 28:52.605
I got a little peak
at the dress. I'm certain
she's a shoo-in for princess.

28:52.689 --> 28:55.400
- She is.
- But tonight,

28:55.484 --> 28:59.612
[Voice Fading] we are very
glad to welcome her young
friend, quarterback no less-

28:59.696 --> 29:02.156
I have to go to the bathroom.

29:02.241 --> 29:05.159
Uh, too much pop.

29:07.329 --> 29:09.872
Oh, wait.
It's right through
the kitchen, sweetheart.

29:11.500 --> 29:13.835
He wears a helmet
when he plays, right?

29:13.919 --> 29:15.878
He's just intimidated
by you, Daddy.

29:17.589 --> 29:21.259
[Panting]

29:21.343 --> 29:24.387
[Cell Phone Rings]

29:24.471 --> 29:26.389
Well, hello, Finn Hudson.

29:26.473 --> 29:30.017
I'm at the Fabrays and
I'm freaking out. What does
a heart attack feel like?

29:30.102 --> 29:33.020
Settle down, cowboy.
This is why we burnt the disc
and spent that time rehearsing.

29:33.105 --> 29:35.857
- I can't do it.
- Yes, you can. Just remember
the power of the ballad.

29:35.941 --> 29:38.776
I have to go.
They'll think I'm pooping.

29:38.861 --> 29:40.695
[Cell Phone Beeps]

29:41.822 --> 29:44.740
[Panting]

29:44.825 --> 29:46.909
[Grunts]

29:46.994 --> 29:49.245
[Grunting]
Ha!

29:53.041 --> 29:56.169
- That's my kitchen radio.
- Yeah, I need to borrow it.

29:56.253 --> 29:58.421
Finn? What's this?

29:58.505 --> 30:01.757
Well, we have this assignment
in Glee Club to sing a ballad.

30:01.842 --> 30:05.678
They're all about expressing
the things you can't find
any other way to say.

30:05.762 --> 30:08.055
Oh, God. Finn, don't.

30:08.140 --> 30:12.226
- Please, don't.
- No, I need to do this...
for both of us.

30:15.564 --> 30:18.566
♪♪ [Ballad]

30:20.319 --> 30:22.570
♪ You're havin' my baby ♪

30:24.490 --> 30:29.285
♪ What a lovely way of sayin'
how much you love me ♪

30:30.537 --> 30:32.413
♪ You're havin' my baby ♪

30:33.707 --> 30:36.209
♪ What a lovely way of sayin' ♪

30:36.293 --> 30:38.419
♪ What you're thinkin' of me ♪

30:39.963 --> 30:41.756
♪ I can see it ♪

30:43.383 --> 30:46.385
♪ Your face is glowin' ♪

30:46.470 --> 30:49.138
♪ I can see it
in your eyes ♪

30:49.223 --> 30:52.016
♪ I'm happy you know it ♪

30:52.100 --> 30:54.268
♪ That you're havin'
my baby ♪

30:55.938 --> 31:00.483
♪ You're the woman I love
and I love what
it's doin' to ya ♪

31:01.902 --> 31:03.778
♪ You're havin' my baby ♪

31:05.656 --> 31:10.993
♪ You're a woman in love
and I love what's
goin' through ya ♪

31:11.078 --> 31:14.455
♪ The need inside you ♪

31:14.540 --> 31:16.624
♪ I see it showin' ♪

31:18.210 --> 31:21.003
♪ Whoa, the seed
inside you, baby ♪

31:21.088 --> 31:23.089
♪♪ [Stops]

31:40.482 --> 31:44.735
There must be some sort
of mistake here.
Quinny, we raised you right.

31:44.820 --> 31:48.406
You— You did.
We didn't even have sex.

31:48.490 --> 31:51.325
I'm sorry. Can we just stop
with the lying, please?

31:51.410 --> 31:54.579
- But I'm-
- When you were about
five years old,

31:54.663 --> 31:57.707
I took you and your sister
down to an Indians game.

31:57.791 --> 31:59.917
All the other dads
brought their sons.

32:00.002 --> 32:02.837
But my two girls
were enough for me.

32:04.214 --> 32:07.967
Daddy.
Your sister made it
through the whole game.

32:08.051 --> 32:10.928
But you fell asleep
in my lap.

32:11.013 --> 32:13.973
I kept hoping nothing
exciting would happen...

32:14.057 --> 32:17.310
'cause I didn't want
the crowd to get too loud...

32:19.271 --> 32:21.272
and wake you up.

32:25.944 --> 32:27.945
Didn't matter.

32:29.948 --> 32:32.366
You stayed asleep
in my arms...

32:33.702 --> 32:35.828
till the game ended.

32:35.912 --> 32:39.165
Daddy, I'm so sorry.

32:39.249 --> 32:42.209
[Sighs]

32:43.420 --> 32:45.171
You need to leave.

32:45.255 --> 32:49.634
Wait. Please, Daddy,
can we talk about this?

32:49.718 --> 32:51.886
Finn is a good guy.

32:51.970 --> 32:53.679
He loves me.

32:53.764 --> 32:55.598
You too.

32:55.682 --> 32:59.185
- [Shuddering]
- Get out of my house.

32:59.269 --> 33:01.312
But you can't do that.
She didn't do anything wrong.

33:01.396 --> 33:04.190
- [Sighs]
- Please, Mrs. Fabray,
do something.

33:04.274 --> 33:07.818
Don't bother, Finn.
[Inhales Sharply]

33:07.903 --> 33:11.906
If she wanted to do something,
she would have when she
found out that I was pregnant.

33:12.824 --> 33:14.283
You knew?

33:15.827 --> 33:18.454
I— No.
She didn't tell me anything.

33:18.538 --> 33:22.667
But you knew.
And I needed you.

33:22.751 --> 33:26.295
I needed my mom.
And you were so scared...

33:26.380 --> 33:28.673
of what he would do...

33:28.757 --> 33:31.884
if he found out that
you just pushed it aside...

33:31.968 --> 33:36.472
like we do every bad feeling
in this house.

33:36.556 --> 33:39.350
If you don't talk about it,
it doesn't exist.

33:39.434 --> 33:41.477
Now do not turn this on us!

33:41.561 --> 33:43.854
You are
the disappointment here!

33:43.939 --> 33:45.940
Why?

33:48.402 --> 33:51.529
Because I'm not
a little girl anymore?

33:52.531 --> 33:54.448
Because I made a mistake?

33:54.533 --> 33:56.659
Who are you?

33:58.286 --> 34:00.287
I don't recognize you
at all.

34:00.372 --> 34:02.456
I'm your daughter...

34:04.042 --> 34:05.501
who loves you.

34:05.585 --> 34:08.254
And I know this must be
really hard for you.

34:08.338 --> 34:13.509
But I just need my daddy
to hold me and tell me
that it's gonna be okay.

34:24.354 --> 34:26.147
Please.

34:27.315 --> 34:29.984
[Sobs]

34:31.653 --> 34:34.196
[Footsteps Climbing Stairs]
Judy!

34:42.456 --> 34:46.375
Honey, how many times have I
told you you gotta turn these
T-shirts right-side out—

34:46.460 --> 34:50.880
Um, Mom, Quinn's parents
threw her out.

34:52.382 --> 34:54.842
Could she stay here
for a couple of days?

34:57.262 --> 34:59.513
Yeah, of course she can.

35:01.641 --> 35:03.726
Honey, you can stay here
as long as you want.

35:08.607 --> 35:11.692
Hey, Barbra Streisand.
We need to have
a little talk.

35:11.777 --> 35:13.694
I have nothing to say
to you, Pepper.

35:13.779 --> 35:15.863
If you continue to stalk me,
I'll press charges.

35:15.947 --> 35:19.200
Everyone knows what you are.
You're the school crazy.

35:19.284 --> 35:21.786
I was crazy-
crazy in love.

35:21.870 --> 35:24.622
There's nothing you can say
that's gonna change the way
I feel about Mr. Schuester.

35:24.706 --> 35:28.250
Ours is a love for the ages.
Your threats will just make
our love grow stronger.

35:28.335 --> 35:31.629
Let me tell you a few things
I learned from two years
of intense psychotherapy...

35:31.713 --> 35:33.964
and an esophagus
transplant.

35:34.049 --> 35:37.426
Lesson number one:
You and Schue,
it won't work.

