What do you mean?

35:39.721 --> 35:42.431
We're not so different,
you and me.

35:42.516 --> 35:45.559
We're both mildly attractive
and extremely grating.

35:45.644 --> 35:47.853
Love is hard for us.

35:47.938 --> 35:49.855
We look for boys
we know we can never have.

35:49.940 --> 35:53.734
Mr. Schue is
a perfect target for
our self-esteem issues.

35:53.819 --> 35:56.654
He can never reciprocate
our feelings, which only
reinforces the conviction...

35:56.738 --> 35:59.698
that we're not worthy
of being loved.

35:59.783 --> 36:03.536
Trust me.
I'm a cautionary tale.

36:05.330 --> 36:08.582
You need to find
some self-respect, Rachel.

36:08.667 --> 36:12.461
Get that mildly attractive
groove back.

36:27.269 --> 36:29.478
Mr. Schuester,
I'm ready when you are.

36:29.563 --> 36:32.356
